ich\naffects the evolution of the Hubble parameter thereby spoiling consistency of\nthe model with data. As for, quasi-dilaton nonlinear massive gravity, the\neffective pressure of matter can be kept around zero by controlling the\ncoupling constant, the model is shown to be fit well with observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Sep 2013 07:19:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 5 Mar 2014 14:28:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-04-09"}
