{"id":"1310.1237","submitter":"Sandeep Kumar Jain","authors":"S.K. Jain, P. Srivastava","title":"Strain energy calculations of hexagonal boron nanotubes: An ab-initio\n  approach","comments":"7 pages, 4 figures","journal-ref":"Condens. Matter Phys., 2013, vol. 16, No. 3, 33802","doi":"10.5488/CMP.16.33802","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.mes-hall cond-mat.mtrl-sci","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  An ab initio calculations have been carried out for examining the curvature\neffect of small diameter hexagonal boron nanotubes. The considered\nconformations of boron nanotubes are namely armchair (3,3), zigzag (5,0) and\nchiral (4,2), and consist of 12, 20, and 56 atoms, respectively. The strain\nenergy is evaluated in order to examine the curvature effect. It is found that\nthe strain energy of hexagonal BNT strongly depends upon the radius, whereas\nthe strain energy of triangular BNTs depends on both radius and chirality.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Sep 2013 10:19:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-10-07"}
